text: All the queens of my acquaintance
a little king with a great throne , like many other kings
my real , live , flesh - and - blood princess
the most unfortunate woman in the world
one of her attendants , who held her by the hand . Spying her father at the other side of the lawn
a princess with such a funny papa
the only person that had any sense in
two of her ladies - in - waiting
a princess who had no gravity
the loveliest lake in the world
his daughter , who was a great favourite with her , was in it with her father
the son of a king , who lived a thousand miles from Lagobel
a fine , handsome , brave , generous , well - bred , and well - behaved youth , as all princes are
a princess that had lost her gravity
the only perfect creature I ever saw
the only person in my father 's kingdom
the mountains which surrounded the lake on all sides
a sort of cave in the rock , where he provided himself a bed of withered leaves , and lay down too tired for hunger to keep him awake
streamers of a great many more
the prince , burned up with the heat
all the radiant company , only one white speck
a deeper and bluer lake than
the higher side of the lake
all the babies throughout the country
the very centre of the lake
a rocky basin of considerable depth
a hermit whom he had met there on his way to Lagobel
the only man who was willing to be useful in the present emergency
a world that has no well , Darkly bright in forest dell
a world without the gleam Of the downward - going stream
a world where never rain Glittered on the sunny plain;-- Such , my heart
a world without the sound Of the rivulets underground
the landing - stairs of the palace
the chamberlain , who , roused by the noise
